  "dateModified": "2018-01-20",
  "datePublished": "2018-01-20",
  "description": "After facing criticism from users, politicians, bureaucrats, and shareholders, Facebook\u0026rsquo;s CEO Mark Zuckerberg announced his personal 2018 New Year\u0026rsquo;s Resolution, to \u0026ldquo;fix Facebook.\u0026rdquo; In previous years, Zuckerberg has publicly announced his resolutions, and his followthrough. He\u0026rsquo;s visited every U.S. state, built an artificial intelligence for his home, ran 365 miles, and learned Mandarin. So I had some hope that he\u0026rsquo;d be able to complete this one - after all, as CEO, \u0026ldquo;fixing Facebook\u0026rdquo; should be a core part of his job.\n",
  "name": "Facebook learned nothing",
